  MBOMBELA – An SAPS sergeant was arrested after he allegedly raped a 17-year-old. The girl was at the Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court for shoplifting when the sergeant allegedly took her away from other detainees. He has appeared in court, but was released on bail of R500. READ ALSO: Man arrested for rape and murder of eight-year-old girl He is scheduled to appear again on October 30. Police spokesman, Lt Col Erhard Stroh, confirmed the sergeant’s appearance in court as well as the charges against him. This is a developing story. Lowvelder will keep you up to date as soon as more information becomes available. READ ALSO: Stepfather accused of rape and grooming 11-year-old with porn, gets R1 000 bail